{"insight":"Every Path Trains Its Own Seeing","plainSummary":"The way we practice shapes the kind of freedom we can recognize.","atAGlance":"A path trains us to meet the change it asks of us. Attention, honesty, trust, and longing are not neutral tools. Each one is shaped toward a different letting go. When we borrow a practice, we also borrow its direction.","match":["grain of capacity"],"tags":["practice","attention","insight","freedom"]}
